HEADWORD: gladdon
<hw>glad"don</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An iris (<spn>Iris
foetidissima</spn>) with purple flowers and evil-smelling leaves;
Southern and Western Europe and North Africa.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gladen, stinking iris, gladdon iris, stinking
gladwyn, roast beef plant, <spn>Iris foetidissima</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

